There is an Opportunity..<br> Daiki Group (A Japanese Organization) is looking forward to recruit people from our Faculty every year.. and they wanna start from our Batch..<br> They are offering IT related job opportunities (exact positions will be confirmed on next Monday), to work in Japan. And for that the candidates should learn Japanese, and they will provide a Japanese course for us after all academic activities..</p><p> The process is.. They will conduct a Japanese course at<span class="text_exposed_hide">...</span><span class="text_exposed_show"> Faculty premises for about 2 months (May change depending on student preferences, late evenings or weekends).. Anybody who wants to learn Japanese can join the course, it is freely offered.. After that, they will have 2 screening processes to test our Japanese knowledge and basic IT knowledge.. And they will recruit the selected candidates (They are expecting to recruit a higher number, more than 10 as per the discussion)..</span></p><span class="text_exposed_hide"> <span
